      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Sorry for the delay, I was OOO today.\n\nNo worries!\n\n\u003e Do we have more info on what device this is happening on?\n\nI believe it happens on the following devices:\n- mentioned by others in the bug:\n  - Bramble\n  - Coral\n- I\u0027ve tested manually:\n  - Blueline\n  - Flame\n\nThe bug also mentioned that it did not happen on a Sunfish, but that was running a QT build. I\u0027m not aware of whether there are devices it does not affect, but these are all Pixels. (Stan tested on a non-Pixel device, but it\u0027s his personal phone, which I believe is running QT or earlier.\n\n\u003e What\u0027s the exact issue?\n\n- Clip to a round rect/path. (On Android, this results in an AA clip, which may be important.)\n- Draw a WebView\n- Sometimes the WebView simply doesn\u0027t draw, so it flickers\n\nMore details in b/156413480",
